            <title>[CASSANDRA-1036] Attempting to mutate a non-existant CF does not propagate an error to the client</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-1036</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;An error gets logged on the server:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;ERROR 15:23:21,035 Attempting to mutate non-existant column family Standard1&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;But nothing is raised on the client side, so it appears the request succeeded.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
